{
  "text": "The phylogeny and evolution of MERS-CoV has been studied through whole genome sequencing of samples from several geographic regions (appendix). In one instance, four diff erent MERS-CoV phylogenetic clades were identifi ed in patients in Saudi Arabia from September, 2012, to May, 2013. [CITATION_1] However, by the end of the observation period, three of these clades were no longer circulating, consistent with an R o of less than 1. Furthermore, the extent of diff erence between these genetically distinct lineages makes it unlikely that the infections were the result of a single continuous chain of human-to-human transmission.",
